How to run ThingsBoard UI (localhost:4200) with local backend

Prerequisites
- Java 17
- Maven
- Node.js + yarn
- PostgreSQL running

1) Build backend from source
cd ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard
mvn clean install -DskipTests

2) Initialize database with demo data (one time)
cd ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard/application/target/bin/install
sudo bash install_dev_db.sh

3) Start backend (recommended script)
~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard/run-backend.sh

Wait until you see:
Started ThingsboardServerApplication

4) Start UI (localhost:4200)
cd ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard/ui-ngx
yarn start

Alternative: run backend manually (Terminal 1)
cd ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard
export LOADER_PATH=application/target/conf,application/target/extensions
export EDGES_RPC_PORT=7071
export MQTT_ENABLED=false
export COAP_ENABLED=false
export LWM2M_ENABLED=false
export SNMP_ENABLED=false
java -Dspring.config.additional-location=application/target/conf/ \
     -jar application/target/thingsboard-*-boot.jar

Then run UI in another terminal (Terminal 2)
cd ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard/ui-ngx
yarn start

5) Login
- URL: http://localhost:4200
- Username: sysadmin@thingsboard.org
- Password: sysadmin

Checks & troubleshooting
- Check backend is listening:
  ss -lntp | grep ':8080'

- If backend fails to start:
  tail -n 80 ~/Thingsboard_mine/thingsboard/application/target/logs/thingsboard.log

- Common port conflicts:
  7070 (Edge RPC), 1883 (MQTT), 5683-5688 (CoAP/LwM2M)
  The run-backend.sh script disables MQTT/CoAP/LwM2M/SNMP and uses EDGES_RPC_PORT=7071.
